76/*
77 * Maximum length of X509_NAME: much larger than anything we should
78 * ever see in practice.
79 */

81#define X509_NAME_MAX (1024 * 1024)

99ASN1_SEQUENCE(X509_NAME_ENTRY) = {
100 ASN1_SIMPLE(X509_NAME_ENTRY, object, ASN1_OBJECT),
101 ASN1_SIMPLE(X509_NAME_ENTRY, value, ASN1_PRINTABLE)
102} ASN1_SEQUENCE_END(X509_NAME_ENTRY)
103
104IMPLEMENT_ASN1_FUNCTIONS(X509_NAME_ENTRY)
105IMPLEMENT_ASN1_DUP_FUNCTION(X509_NAME_ENTRY)
106
107/*
108 * For the "Name" type we need a SEQUENCE OF { SET OF X509_NAME_ENTRY } so
109 * declare two template wrappers for this
110 */
111
112ASN1_ITEM_TEMPLATE(X509_NAME_ENTRIES) =
113 ASN1_EX_TEMPLATE_TYPE(ASN1_TFLG_SET_OF, 0, RDNS, X509_NAME_ENTRY)
114ASN1_ITEM_TEMPLATE_END(X509_NAME_ENTRIES)
115
116ASN1_ITEM_TEMPLATE(X509_NAME_INTERNAL) =
117 ASN1_EX_TEMPLATE_TYPE(ASN1_TFLG_SEQUENCE_OF, 0, Name, X509_NAME_ENTRIES)
118ASN1_ITEM_TEMPLATE_END(X509_NAME_INTERNAL)
119
120/*
121 * Normally that's where it would end: we'd have two nested STACK structures
122 * representing the ASN1. Unfortunately X509_NAME uses a completely different
123 * form and caches encodings so we have to process the internal form and
124 * convert to the external form.
125 */
126
127static const ASN1_EXTERN_FUNCS x509_name_ff = {
128 NULL,
129 x509_name_ex_new,
130 x509_name_ex_free,
131 0, /* Default clear behaviour is OK */
132 x509_name_ex_d2i,
133 x509_name_ex_i2d,
134 NULL,
135};
136
137IMPLEMENT_EXTERN_ASN1(X509_NAME, V_ASN1_SEQUENCE, x509_name_ff)

139IMPLEMENT_ASN1_FUNCTIONS(X509_NAME)
140
141IMPLEMENT_ASN1_DUP_FUNCTION(X509_NAME)
142
143static int x509_name_ex_new(ASN1_VALUE **val, const ASN1_ITEM *it)
144{
145 X509_NAME *ret = NULL;
146 ret = OPENSSL_malloc(sizeof(X509_NAME));
147 if (!ret)
148 goto memerr;
149 if ((ret->entries = sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_new_null()) == NULL)
150 goto memerr;
151 if ((ret->bytes = BUF_MEM_new()) == NULL)
152 goto memerr;
153 ret->canon_enc = NULL;
154 ret->canon_enclen = 0;
155 ret->modified = 1;
156 *val = (ASN1_VALUE *)ret;
157 return 1;
158
159 memerr:
160 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
161 if (ret) {
162 if (ret->entries)
163 sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_free(ret->entries);
164 OPENSSL_free(ret);
165 }
166 return 0;
167}
168
169static void x509_name_ex_free(ASN1_VALUE **pval, const ASN1_ITEM *it)
170{
171 X509_NAME *a;
172 if (!pval || !*pval)
173 return;
174 a = (X509_NAME *)*pval;
175
176 BUF_MEM_free(a->bytes);
177 sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_pop_free(a->entries, X509_NAME_ENTRY_free);
178 if (a->canon_enc)
179 OPENSSL_free(a->canon_enc);
180 OPENSSL_free(a);
181 *pval = NULL;
182}

184static void local_sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_free(STACK_OF(X509_NAME_ENTRY) *ne)
185{
186 sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_free(ne);
187}
188
189static void local_sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_pop_free(STACK_OF(X509_NAME_ENTRY) *ne)
190{
191 sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_pop_free(ne, X509_NAME_ENTRY_free);
192}

194static int x509_name_ex_d2i(ASN1_VALUE **val,
195 const unsigned char **in, long len,
196 const ASN1_ITEM *it, int tag, int aclass,
197 char opt, ASN1_TLC *ctx)
198{
199 const unsigned char *p = *in, *q;
200 STACK_OF(STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY) *intname = NULL;
201 X509_NAME *nm = NULL;
202 size_t i, j;
203 int ret;
204 STACK_OF(X509_NAME_ENTRY) *entries;
205 X509_NAME_ENTRY *entry;
206 /* Bound the size of an X509_NAME we are willing to parse. */
207 if (len > X509_NAME_MAX) {
208 len = X509_NAME_MAX;
209 }
210 q = p;
211
212 /* Get internal representation of Name */
213 ASN1_VALUE *intname_val = NULL;
214 ret = ASN1_item_ex_d2i(&intname_val,
215 &p, len, ASN1_ITEM_rptr(X509_NAME_INTERNAL),
216 tag, aclass, opt, ctx);
217 if (ret <= 0)
218 return ret;
219 intname = (STACK_OF(STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY) *)intname_val;
220
221 if (*val)
222 x509_name_ex_free(val, NULL);
223 ASN1_VALUE *nm_val = NULL;
224 if (!x509_name_ex_new(&nm_val, NULL))
225 goto err;
226 nm = (X509_NAME *)nm_val;
227 /* We've decoded it: now cache encoding */
228 if (!BUF_MEM_grow(nm->bytes, p - q))
229 goto err;
230 OPENSSL_memcpy(nm->bytes->data, q, p - q);
231
232 /* Convert internal representation to X509_NAME structure */
233 for (i = 0; i < sk_STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY_num(intname); i++) {
234 entries = sk_STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY_value(intname, i);
235 for (j = 0; j < sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_num(entries); j++) {
236 entry = sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_value(entries, j);
237 entry->set = i;
238 if (!sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_push(nm->entries, entry))
239 goto err;
240 (void)sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_set(entries, j, NULL);
241 }
242 }
243 ret = x509_name_canon(nm);
244 if (!ret)
245 goto err;
246 sk_STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY_pop_free(intname,
247 local_sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_free);
248 nm->modified = 0;
249 *val = (ASN1_VALUE *)nm;
250 *in = p;
251 return ret;
252 err:
253 X509_NAME_free(nm);
254 sk_STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY_pop_free(intname,
255 local_sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_pop_free);
256 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, ERR_R_ASN1_LIB);
257 return 0;
258}
259
260static int x509_name_ex_i2d(ASN1_VALUE **val, unsigned char **out,
261 const ASN1_ITEM *it, int tag, int aclass)
262{
263 int ret;
264 X509_NAME *a = (X509_NAME *)*val;
265 if (a->modified) {
266 ret = x509_name_encode(a);
267 if (ret < 0)
268 return ret;
269 ret = x509_name_canon(a);
270 if (ret < 0)
271 return ret;
272 }
273 ret = a->bytes->length;
274 if (out != NULL) {
275 OPENSSL_memcpy(*out, a->bytes->data, ret);
276 *out += ret;
277 }
278 return ret;
279}
280
281static int x509_name_encode(X509_NAME *a)
282{
283 int len;
284 unsigned char *p;
285 STACK_OF(X509_NAME_ENTRY) *entries = NULL;
286 X509_NAME_ENTRY *entry;
287 int set = -1;
288 size_t i;
289 STACK_OF(STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY) *intname =
290 sk_STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY_new_null();
291 if (!intname)
292 goto memerr;
293 for (i = 0; i < sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_num(a->entries); i++) {
294 entry = sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_value(a->entries, i);
295 if (entry->set != set) {
296 entries = sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_new_null();
297 if (!entries)
298 goto memerr;
299 if (!sk_STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY_push(intname, entries)) {
300 sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_free(entries);
301 goto memerr;
302 }
303 set = entry->set;
304 }
305 if (!sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_push(entries, entry))
306 goto memerr;
307 }
308 ASN1_VALUE *intname_val = (ASN1_VALUE *)intname;
309 len = ASN1_item_ex_i2d(&intname_val, NULL,
310 ASN1_ITEM_rptr(X509_NAME_INTERNAL), -1, -1);
311 if (!BUF_MEM_grow(a->bytes, len))
312 goto memerr;
313 p = (unsigned char *)a->bytes->data;
314 ASN1_item_ex_i2d(&intname_val,
315 &p, ASN1_ITEM_rptr(X509_NAME_INTERNAL), -1, -1);
316 sk_STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY_pop_free(intname,
317 local_sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_free);
318 a->modified = 0;
319 return len;
320 memerr:
321 sk_STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY_pop_free(intname,
322 local_sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_free);
323 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
324 return -1;
325}
326
327/*
328 * This function generates the canonical encoding of the Name structure. In
329 * it all strings are converted to UTF8, leading, trailing and multiple
330 * spaces collapsed, converted to lower case and the leading SEQUENCE header
331 * removed. In future we could also normalize the UTF8 too. By doing this
332 * comparison of Name structures can be rapidly perfomed by just using
333 * OPENSSL_memcmp() of the canonical encoding. By omitting the leading SEQUENCE name
334 * constraints of type dirName can also be checked with a simple OPENSSL_memcmp().
335 */
336
337static int x509_name_canon(X509_NAME *a)
338{
339 unsigned char *p;
340 STACK_OF(STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY) *intname = NULL;
341 STACK_OF(X509_NAME_ENTRY) *entries = NULL;
342 X509_NAME_ENTRY *entry, *tmpentry = NULL;
343 int set = -1, ret = 0, len;
344 size_t i;
345
346 if (a->canon_enc) {
347 OPENSSL_free(a->canon_enc);
348 a->canon_enc = NULL;
349 }
350 /* Special case: empty X509_NAME => null encoding */
351 if (sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_num(a->entries) == 0) {
352 a->canon_enclen = 0;
353 return 1;
354 }
355 intname = sk_STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY_new_null();
356 if (!intname)
357 goto err;
358 for (i = 0; i < sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_num(a->entries); i++) {
359 entry = sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_value(a->entries, i);
360 if (entry->set != set) {
361 entries = sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_new_null();
362 if (!entries)
363 goto err;
364 if (!sk_STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY_push(intname, entries)) {
365 sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_free(entries);
366 goto err;
367 }
368 set = entry->set;
369 }
370 tmpentry = X509_NAME_ENTRY_new();
371 if (tmpentry == NULL)
372 goto err;
373 tmpentry->object = OBJ_dup(entry->object);
374 if (!asn1_string_canon(tmpentry->value, entry->value))
375 goto err;
376 if (!sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_push(entries, tmpentry))
377 goto err;
378 tmpentry = NULL;
379 }
380
381 /* Finally generate encoding */
382
383 len = i2d_name_canon(intname, NULL);
384 if (len < 0) {
385 goto err;
386 }
387 a->canon_enclen = len;
388
389 p = OPENSSL_malloc(a->canon_enclen);
390
391 if (!p)
392 goto err;
393
394 a->canon_enc = p;
395
396 i2d_name_canon(intname, &p);
397
398 ret = 1;
399
400 err:
401
402 if (tmpentry)
403 X509_NAME_ENTRY_free(tmpentry);
404 if (intname)
405 sk_STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY_pop_free(intname,
406 local_sk_X509_NAME_ENTRY_pop_free);
407 return ret;
408}
409
410/* Bitmap of all the types of string that will be canonicalized. */
411
412#define ASN1_MASK_CANON \
413 (B_ASN1_UTF8STRING | B_ASN1_BMPSTRING | B_ASN1_UNIVERSALSTRING \
414 | B_ASN1_PRINTABLESTRING | B_ASN1_T61STRING | B_ASN1_IA5STRING \
415 | B_ASN1_VISIBLESTRING)
416
417static int asn1_string_canon(ASN1_STRING *out, ASN1_STRING *in)
418{
419 unsigned char *to, *from;
420 int len, i;
421
422 /* If type not in bitmask just copy string across */
423 if (!(ASN1_tag2bit(in->type) & ASN1_MASK_CANON)) {
424 if (!ASN1_STRING_copy(out, in))
425 return 0;
426 return 1;
427 }
428
429 out->type = V_ASN1_UTF8STRING;
430 out->length = ASN1_STRING_to_UTF8(&out->data, in);
431 if (out->length == -1)
432 return 0;
433
434 to = out->data;
435 from = to;
436
437 len = out->length;
438
439 /*
440 * Convert string in place to canonical form. Ultimately we may need to
441 * handle a wider range of characters but for now ignore anything with
442 * MSB set and rely on the isspace() and tolower() functions.
443 */
444
445 /* Ignore leading spaces */
446 while ((len > 0) && !(*from & 0x80) && isspace(*from)) {
447 from++;
448 len--;
449 }
450
451 to = from + len;
452
453 /* Ignore trailing spaces */
454 while ((len > 0) && !(to[-1] & 0x80) && isspace(to[-1])) {
455 to--;
456 len--;
457 }
458
459 to = out->data;
460
461 i = 0;
462 while (i < len) {
463 /* If MSB set just copy across */
464 if (*from & 0x80) {
465 *to++ = *from++;
466 i++;
467 }
468 /* Collapse multiple spaces */
469 else if (isspace(*from)) {
470 /* Copy one space across */
471 *to++ = ' ';
472 /*
473 * Ignore subsequent spaces. Note: don't need to check len here
474 * because we know the last character is a non-space so we can't
475 * overflow.
476 */
477 do {
478 from++;
479 i++;
480 }
481 while (!(*from & 0x80) && isspace(*from));
482 } else {
483 *to++ = OPENSSL_tolower(*from);
484 from++;
485 i++;
486 }
487 }
488
489 out->length = to - out->data;
490
491 return 1;
492
493}
494
495static int i2d_name_canon(STACK_OF(STACK_OF_X509_NAME_ENTRY) * _intname,
496 unsigned char **in)
497{
498 int len, ltmp;
499 size_t i;
500 ASN1_VALUE *v;
501 STACK_OF(ASN1_VALUE) *intname = (STACK_OF(ASN1_VALUE) *)_intname;
502
503 len = 0;
504 for (i = 0; i < sk_ASN1_VALUE_num(intname); i++) {
505 v = sk_ASN1_VALUE_value(intname, i);
506 ltmp = ASN1_item_ex_i2d(&v, in,
507 ASN1_ITEM_rptr(X509_NAME_ENTRIES), -1, -1);
508 if (ltmp < 0)
509 return ltmp;
510 len += ltmp;
511 }
512 return len;
513}
514
515int X509_NAME_set(X509_NAME **xn, X509_NAME *name)
516{
517 if ((name = X509_NAME_dup(name)) == NULL)
518 return 0;
519 X509_NAME_free(*xn);
520 *xn = name;
521 return 1;
522}

524IMPLEMENT_ASN1_SET_OF(X509_NAME_ENTRY)
525
526int X509_NAME_ENTRY_set(const X509_NAME_ENTRY *ne)
527{
528 return ne->set;
529}

531int X509_NAME_get0_der(X509_NAME *nm, const unsigned char **pder,
532 size_t *pderlen)
533{
534 /* Make sure encoding is valid */
535 if (i2d_X509_NAME(nm, NULL) <= 0)
536 return 0;
537 if (pder != NULL)
538 *pder = (unsigned char *)nm->bytes->data;
539 if (pderlen != NULL)
540 *pderlen = nm->bytes->length;
541 return 1;
542}
